1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Ladybug and Cat Noir have saved Paris once again.

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:07,000
And once again, Marinette tries to find time to complete her magic box.

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:09,000
What's the magic box for, Marinette?

4
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:11,000
To keep all my heart's secrets.

5
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:12,000
All your secrets?

6
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
So you write everything you do in that notebook?

7
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:17,000
Oh, yes. Is there a problem?

8
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:23,000
Yeah, like what if someone finds out you're Ladybug... also, someone could find out you're Ladybug.

9
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,000
That will never happen. Just take a try Tikki.

12
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,000
And it worked.

13
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:34,000
The other day, Mr. Bourgeois was elected mayor of Paris, starting his fourth term.

14
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:36,000
Here's Mr. Bourgeois with his daughter in public.

15
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Oh, look at Chloé, as if she's the mayor of Paris. Oh, speaking of which, the class president election is tomorrow.

16
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:45,000
What's wrong with that, Marinette?

17
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Because Chloé is going to run too.

18
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:51,000
She's someone who thinks of herself the most, and the students the least.

19
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:53,000
Well, then you should run.

20
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:58,000
I'd like to, but with my duties as Ladybug... and I already have homework.

21
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:01,000
True, but if you believe in something enough, you fight for it.

22
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Better to try and fail than not try at all.

23
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:04,500
Maybe.

24
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:07,000
Don't put yourself down, Marinette.

25
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Armand D'Argencourt, Bourgeois's main opponent... and your fencing teacher at François Dupont High School, was crushed at the polls.

26
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:18,000
In fact, D'Argencourt got the fewest votes in Paris history.

27
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:21,000
I'm about to be late for school.

28
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:21,500
Again.

29
00:01:21,500 --> 00:01:25,000
See, that's what I'm talking about.

30
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Chloé is announcing her candidacy for class president.

31
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,000
And her running mate will be Sabrina.

32
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:31,000
Any other candidates?

33
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:31,500
Hmm.

34
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:32,000
Hmm.

35
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,000
Yes, who?

36
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Uh, no.

37
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Oh, sorry, I was on the bus... Oh, my throat is dry.

38
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Chloé is running again.

39
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,000
How long has she been class president?

40
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,000
Since kindergarten?

41
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,000
Why don't you run?

42
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:49,000
You'd be a great president.

43
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:50,000
No way.

44
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,000
I'm constantly dealing with Chloé.

45
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Alright.

46
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:55,000
I'll give you all until noon to think about running.

47
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,000
Don't ever do that again.

48
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:59,000
I hate being treated like that.

49
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,000
What are you girls doing?

50
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:03,000
What did Chloé say to you this time?

51
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,000
She wants to go out with you?

52
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,000
No, she told everyone I'm afraid of spiders.

53
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:12,000
They told me that if I run... they'll kick me out of the scrapbooking club.

54
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:16,000
But I love those stickers, decorations, glitter.

55
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:18,000
I don't even care about being a candidate.

56
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,000
What's your excuse?

57
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,000
I'm too busy.

58
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,000
With what?

59
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Sleeping?

60
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:34,000
Oh no, but uh, well, if no one else is going to run... maybe...

61
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Alright, any other candidates against Chloé and Sabrina?

62
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:46,000
Since Chloé and Sabrina are the only candidates, I guess there's no need for a vote.

63
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:50,000
So Chloé and Sabrina... I'm running!

64
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,000
Great.

65
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:54,000
By tomorrow, you'll need to prepare a campaign speech and work on your presentation.

66
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,000
Then the election begins.

67
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,000
I can't believe this.

68
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:01,000
Yes, let's hear the big surprise of your campaign.

69
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,000
How will you introduce yourself?

70
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,000
Introduce myself?

71
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:07,000
I have no idea, but I can't believe I raised my hand.

72
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:09,000
You're amazing, Marinette.

73
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Speak bravely.

74
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,000
This is incredible.

75
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Thank you.

76
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,000
If you win, can we get more comfortable seats?

77
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,000
These are so hard I can't focus on the lesson.

78
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:25,000
Also, pink ones. And if we could listen to music while studying in the library, that would be even better.

79
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:28,000
Actually, I don't know.

80
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Of course, Juleka.

81
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:33,000
Adrien, you're voting for Marinette, right?

82
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:35,000
Sure, but it depends on her speech.

83
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:38,000
I have to run a really good campaign.

84
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:41,000
I've seen my father win every election.

85
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,000
And I can follow in his footsteps.

86
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,000
I know how to win.

87
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,000
With the best campaign, right?

88
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,000
Nonsense.

89
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:52,000
The secret to winning in politics is always to destroy your opponent's reputation.

90
00:03:55,000 --> 00:04:02,000
Comfortable seats, library music, like Juleka said... I'm writing down everyone's problems.

91
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,000
Now I need to add these to my campaign speech.

92
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,000
I'm proud of you.

93
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,000
I'm sure you'll win.

94
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,000
You'll be a great president.

95
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,000
They're counting on me to beat Chloé.

96
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:15,000
Even Adrien... You noticed, right?

97
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,000
Marinette, the battle has begun.

98
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:16,500
What?

99
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:17,000
What's going on?

100
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:20,000
Chloé gathered the whole class at City Hall for an election party.

101
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,000
Plus, there's a Jagged Stone concert.

102
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:23,000
Are you serious?

103
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,000
Jagged Stone is my favorite pop star.

104
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:27,000
I love him.

105
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,000
Of course, everyone loves him.

106
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,000
Absolutely.

107
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:31,000
She's trying to buy votes by giving out autographed photos.

108
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,000
No way, not before I have my say.

109
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:35,000
See you.

110
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,000
I'm coming in, Chloé.

111
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:46,000
Hello.

112
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:46,500
Hello.

113
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:50,000
Marinette borrowed my geometry book, but I need it.

114
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:52,000
Marinette isn't here.

115
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,000
I need to attend to my customer.

116
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:57,000
But if it's no trouble, you can go up and get it from her room yourself.

117
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,000
Oh, no problem.

118
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,000
Thank you.

119
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,000
Nice move.

120
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,000
I have to go.

121
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:20,000
That last move you saw was invented by my great ancestor, Darkblade.

122
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:21,000
Darkblade?

123
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:26,000
In ancient times, Darkblade seized Paris and ruled oppressively.

124
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:32,000
But then the people, bought with money from a wealthy Frenchman, united and overthrew him.

125
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:36,000
That wasn't so long ago, and my ancestors' flag once flew over Paris.

126
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:38,000
Is that why you entered the election, Mr. D'Argencourt?

127
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,000
To avenge your ancestors?

128
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:40,500
Nonsense!

129
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:42,000
Where is this coming from?

130
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:45,000
Nadia Chamack, don't be offended, it's news.

131
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:49,000
How do you comment on your historic defeat that everyone is talking about?

132
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,000
Hey, excuse me, how did you get into the school?

133
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,000
Come on, get out of the studio.

134
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Hey, stop, come back here!

135
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,000
Class is over here.

136
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:02,000
A wimp and a klutz are running for office.

137
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:06,000
But I will present the most suitable candidate to the public.

138
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:14,000
Fly away, my little akuma.

139
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:17,000
Take hold of this defeated warrior.

140
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:28,000
Mr. D'Argencourt, to quote the rumors...

141
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:32,000
They say you're a stubborn, rusty relic of a bygone era.

142
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,000
What do you say to that?

143
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,000
They're slandering me.

144
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:37,000
Why are you bothering with such ridiculous questions?

145
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,000
Get out of here, you nuisances.

146
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Darkblade, in exchange for these powers I give you, you will capture Ladybug and Cat Noir for me.

147
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:04,000
When my ancestors' flag flies once again over Paris City Hall... then I will consider my revenge complete.

148
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:14,000
We're curious, what you just transformed into in front of the cameras... Darkblade, Lord of Paris.

149
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,000
What?

150
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:22,000
Now, become my knights.

151
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:26,000
Soon my army will be ruthless and invincible.

152
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:32,000
We must lay siege to City Hall and take the throne back from that wretch Bourgeois.

153
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:34,000
A medieval nutjob has arrived.

154
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,000
Time to transform.

155
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,000
Plagg, claws out!

156
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,000
Great!

157
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:57,000
A monster that can join our conquest.

158
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,000
To battle!

159
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:09,500
To battle!

160
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:10,000
To battle!

161
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:10,500
To battle!

162
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:11,000
To battle!

163
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:11,500
To battle!

164
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:12,000
To battle!

165
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,000
To battle!

166
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,000
Come on, to battle, my knights!

167
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,000
To battle!

168
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,000
To battle!

169
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:20,000
The people want Bourgeois to rule, not you, D'Argencourt.

170
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,000
I don't care about the people.

171
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:24,000
And D'Argencourt has been defeated.

172
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,000
Not Darkblade, you fool!

173
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,000
Chloé, I'm inside.

174
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:30,000
What was I supposed to look for?

175
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,000
Anything.

176
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,000
As long as it's embarrassing.

177
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:37,000
Wait, I had one of these.

178
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,000
Could it be?

179
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,000
A yo-yo?

180
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,000
Or a screwdriver?

181
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,000
Of course not, you half-wit.

182
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:44,000
It has to be a really bad photo.

183
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,000
Or an ugly dress.

184
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:48,000
Look around a bit.

185
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,000
How about a diary?

186
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,000
Wow.

187
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:54,000
So when you really want something, you can find it.

188
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,000
Sabrina.

189
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,000
Sabrina.

190
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,000
Sabrina.

191
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:07,000
Welcome, everyone, to the official launch of Chloé's election campaign.

192
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:13,000
And special thanks to world star Jagged Stone for supporting Chloé.

193
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:18,000
And when you vote for me, you'll get tickets to Jagged's next concert.

194
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,000
I'm going to be great.

195
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,000
Autographed photos?

196
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:26,500
Yes.

197
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:28,000
I got one for you too.

198
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,000
Sorry, I couldn't help myself.

199
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,000
What?

200
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,000
No, I'm not falling for that.

201
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:36,000
But if you vote for me, I might forgive you.

202
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,000
Are you serious?

203
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,000
How did you not notice that move?

204
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:49,000
Catch them!

205
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,000
Don't waste a single minute.

206
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:56,000
To City Hall, immediately!

207
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,000
City Hall, huh?

208
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:02,000
You go ahead, I'll catch up.

209
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,000
Oh, where have you been?

210
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,000
You got the diary, right, Sabrina?

211
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,000
I got it.

212
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,000
Sort of.

213
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,000
What is this?

214
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:16,000
When I took the diary, this weird box trapped my hand inside it.

215
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:19,000
Do you expect me to believe that?

216
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,000
Who am I kidding?

217
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:22,000
Don't you realize you're being bribed?

218
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:26,000
Concert tickets are great, but this isn't how you solve the class's problems.

219
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,000
So what's in your campaign, Marinette?

220
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:33,000
Well, instead of new seats, I thought we could put cushions.

221
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,000
Your cushion would be pink.

222
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:38,000
And I also thought about the library music.

223
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,000
With headphones, of course.

224
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:41,000
That's incredible.

225
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,000
You're already acting like class president.

226
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:45,000
But unfortunately, you won't win this.

227
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:47,000
Let's talk.

228
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,000
Oh, you took my diary from my room.

229
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:55,000
If you don't drop out of the election, all your secrets will be exposed.

230
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,000
Don't!

231
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,000
I mean, what secrets could they be?

232
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:01,000
Ha, we'll find out soon.

233
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:05,000
But first, I need to find a saw.

234
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,000
Everyone listen up.

235
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,000
Darkblade is about to speak.

236
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:17,000
Anyone who doesn't listen goes to prison.

237
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:21,000
Finally, my flag will fly over this kingdom.

238
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,000
Bourgeois, you wretch.

239
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:25,000
Come and fight me.

240
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:26,000
What is he saying now?

241
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:29,000
Basically, he's going to kill us.

242
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:32,000
Please make an appointment with my secretary.

243
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:34,000
Submit to Darkblade.

244
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:37,000
Or face my wrath.

245
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:37,500
To battle!

246
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:38,000
To battle!

247
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,000
To battle!

248
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,000
To battle!

249
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:49,000
Catch them!

250
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,000
Kids, aren't you tired of metal music?

251
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,000
Cat Noir, quick!

252
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,000
Good warm-up.

253
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:08,000
To battle!

254
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,000
Is that the sound of my crazy fans?

255
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:19,000
I can control them.

256
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,000
Stay out of this, Luka.

257
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,000
Okay, okay.

258
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:39,000
I get it, you love me, but please don't fight.

259
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:41,000
Are you an enemy warrior?

260
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:43,000
I don't understand.

261
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:46,500
No way.

262
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:49,000
What are we going to do?

263
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,000
Quick, to the door.

264
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,000
Quick, to the door.

265
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,000
Enough, Chloé.

266
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:55,000
Enough, Chloé.

267
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,000
Everyone kneel before Darkblade.

268
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,000
You will all obey.

269
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:02,000
Chloé, what are we going to do?

270
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,000
What's the class president going to do?

271
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:07,000
If you vote for me, I might give you an answer.

272
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:07,500
But tomorrow.

273
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:09,000
We can't wait until tomorrow.

274
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,000
Then tough luck.

275
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:12,000
Ask someone else.

276
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:16,000
Well, we need to talk.

277
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:20,000
What are you going to do now?

278
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:23,000
I need to help Cat Noir, but I also need to help the students.

279
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:25,000
You have to trust your instincts.

280
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,000
Ivan, lock the door.

281
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,000
Close all the windows too.

282
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:37,000
Hurry.

283
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:40,000
Nino, Juleka, Rose, Mylène, Alya, you're with me.

284
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,000
Good girl.

285
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:44,000
That's how the future class president is raised.

286
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:47,000
Well, I was going to say the same things to you.

287
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:50,000
Sabrina, Ivan, Kim, go close the door.

288
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:52,000
Move forward.

289
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:57,000
We need to barricade the entrances.

290
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,000
Quick.

291
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:06,000
I hope they haven't done anything bad to Cat Noir.

292
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,000
Time to retreat.

293
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,000
Look, we need to get out of here right now.

294
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,000
This way.

295
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,000
I'll catch up from behind.

296
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,000
I'll close the windows tightly and come.

297
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:17,000
Now they'll be safe.

298
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:19,000
The only ones left.

299
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,000
Out of the way, you garbage fools.

300
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,000
Cat Noir.

301
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,000
I'm here.

302
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:40,000
Sorry, Cat Noir.

303
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:42,000
I had to take care of the people inside.

304
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:45,000
Actually, I was doing just fine on my own.

305
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,000
But it's good to see you, of course.

306
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:48,000
Scutum formation.

307
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,000
Great.

308
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:04,000
Useless jesters.

309
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,000
Let go.

310
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:15,000
Why are they jumping into the moat?

311
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:16,000
Looks like not all of them can jump.

312
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:18,000
The flag.

313
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,000
I hope so.

314
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:28,000
When my own coat of arms replaces this flag, I will be the sovereign.

315
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:32,000
The akuma must be in the sword.

316
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,000
So how do we get the sword?

317
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:35,000
I need to get close to him.

318
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:49,000
Cat Noir must not get the pennant.

319
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:56,000
Jesters, that didn't affect me at all.

320
00:15:56,000 --> 00:16:00,000
Thanks to the Sword of Darkness, everyone within the borders of this kingdom now belongs to me.

321
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,000
Bow to your king!

322
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:33,000
Soon you will join me too.

323
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:35,000
You pathetic insect.

324
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:37,000
There it is. A bit tricky.

325
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:39,000
You fool.

326
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:48,000
Cat Noir and Ladybug will soon face their cursed fate.

327
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:02,000
We are about to become dark knights.

328
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,000
To battle! >> Lucky Charm!

329
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,000
Okay.

330
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,000
Okay.

331
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,000
I hope Darkblade is ticklish.

332
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:31,000
Now you'll see.

333
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:52,000
You can't do evil anymore, akuma.

334
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:58,000
Come on, give up the evil.

335
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:03,000
That's it.

336
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,000
Fly away, little butterfly.

337
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:08,000
Miraculous Ladybug.

338
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:17,000
Pound it!

339
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:20,000
I have to go, see you.

340
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:24,000
Our duel isn't over yet, my Ladybug.

341
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:27,000
When our battle ends, I will win.

342
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,000
You were great, Marinette.

343
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:38,000
You proved that you can be both Ladybug and class president.

344
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:41,000
It wasn't easy, but I'm glad I tried.

345
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:46,000
Because if I hadn't tried, I wouldn't have known I could do it.

346
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:50,000
Where have you been, Marinette?

347
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:52,000
Hiding under a rock?

348
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,000
You're so funny, Chloé.

349
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:55,000
I transformed too.

350
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,000
I became a knight.

351
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,000
Yeah, me too.

352
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,000
What a nightmare, right?

353
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:03,000
Since everything is over, give me back my personal belongings.

354
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:06,000
I honestly have no idea what you're talking about.

355
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:08,000
Please take this.

356
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:15,000
Thank you.

357
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:17,000
Do you have an explanation, Chloé?

358
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,000
I told you.

359
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,000
I didn't take her diary.

360
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:21,000
I don't appreciate you blaming me.

361
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:26,000
Then how do you know there was a diary inside?

362
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:29,000
Well... Sabrina told me.

363
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:30,000
It was all her idea anyway.

364
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:32,000
Not nice.

365
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:35,000
We know no one is going to vote for Chloé now.

366
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:37,000
You'll be the new class president.

367
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:40,000
Let's not rush, Alya.

368
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:42,000
See, she doesn't trust herself.

369
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,000
She's already giving up.

370
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:45,000
No, I'm not.

371
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:47,000
I want to be elected fairly.

372
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:51,000
Not because you don't want Chloé, but because you want me.

373
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:53,000
I don't want to make promises I can't keep.

374
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:56,000
And I can't give you everything you want.

375
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:58,000
But I am resourceful and I know my priorities.

376
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:01,000
I listen well, I can multitask.

377
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:04,000
I truly believe in being your president.

378
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:06,000
And most importantly, I believe in myself.

379
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:11,000
So, votes for the new president, votes for Marinette.

380
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:13,000
What are you doing?

381
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,000
Have you lost your mind?

382
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:19,000
What good are you?

383
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:25,000
By majority vote, Marinette is our new class president.

384
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,000
And Alya is elected her running mate.

385
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:29,000
You can help me deal with Chloé.

386
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,000
If we put our minds to it, we can accomplish anything.

387
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:33,000
I've got your back.